<paragraph id="3A5740429B996147042B4AB18159656A" pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName id="54EFF30C9E95274C2160C3D9A5D882C1" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phalaena roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">Phalaena roraria</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1776, Genera Insect. 285, Europe.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ABE368B272BD5A6E8F85D8EB097D362A" pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName id="7E2AB7568540E7D9402A6190741EFF3A" authority="Linnaeus, 1758" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Phalaena" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Phalaena adspersaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="adspersaria">Phalaena adspersaria</taxonomicName>
Fabricius, 1787, Mantissa Insect. 2: 189, [Germany], [Saxony-Anhalt]: Halae Saxonum [Halle (Saale)].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A619960D2854BD36F4AE7B851E5ACE0A" pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName id="A43BA13B44F9E3BBEEB0EAA6FFD02B2A" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fidonia spartiaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="spartiaria">Fidonia spartiaria</taxonomicName>
Treitschke, 1827, Schmett. Eur. 6 (1): 270, [Germany]: river Rhine [patria falsa?]. The original description (upperside and underside) corresponds to 
<taxonomicName id="1EF6697BA168A4A51A82DD1BE78B81D7" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">roraria</taxonomicName>
, but in the locality indicated only the taxon 
<taxonomicName id="F713213FCC340E8E4D0AAD58C79A4238" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="limbaria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="limbaria">limbaria</taxonomicName>
occurs.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D08085ABD74CAC2B01D7250A7435326" lastPageId="15" lastPageNumber="242" pageId="14" pageNumber="241">
<taxonomicName id="809B63F4561CD3C1741FF4EF648CB4AA" authority="aequestriga" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fidonia roraria subsp. ab." order="Lepidoptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="241" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="roraria" subSpecies="ab.">Fidonia roraria ab. aequestriga</taxonomicName>
Hirschke, 1910, Verh. zool.-bot. Ges. Wien 60: 416, [Czech Republic], Silesia: near Trop 
<pageBreakToken id="44E67979A3E5EEF7A568B3E19ACE1DAA" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" start="start">pau</pageBreakToken>
[Opava] [infrasubspecific: form without dark terminal fascia].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A04B96458A1F4C2FC46021BCAAC6B99F" pageId="15" pageNumber="242">
<taxonomicName id="D1D48E4A7C7F94034EFF739144A7F435" authority="nigrescens" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Fidonia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Fidonia roraria subsp. ab." order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="roraria" subSpecies="ab.">Fidonia roraria ab. nigrescens</taxonomicName>
Preissecker, 1923, Verh. zool.-bot. Ges. Wien 72: (95), [Lower Austria]: Dunkelsteinerwald, near Ernsthof [infrasubspecific].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="FBA8C1C9FB8A234F43D2B6FD81050E0B" pageId="15" pageNumber="242">
? 
<taxonomicName id="89A3BFBD2F7440FF10E12729FD370B8C" authority="Duponchel, 1829" authorityName="Caradja" authorityYear="1930" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cleogene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Cleogene ostrogovichi" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ostrogovichi">Cleogene ostrogovichi</taxonomicName>
Caradja, 1930, Bull. Sect. scient. Acad. roum. 13 (3): 52, [Romania], 
<normalizedToken id="C5D350129693B557503CA587D3AACF8B" originalValue="Siebenbürgen">Siebenbuergen</normalizedToken>
[Transylvania]: Cluj, [
<normalizedToken id="39D35695645196DF2C93724232856215" originalValue="Galişer">Galiser</normalizedToken>
Hill]. Synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="66BE5574D860904AADB2D8317F836E30" authority="Duponchel, 1829" authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cleogene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">roraria</taxonomicName>
according to 
<bibRefCitation id="101DBB2428520279A30AB477D5C442FF" author="Rakosy, L" journalOrPublisher="Entomologica romanica" pageId="17" pageNumber="244" pagination="63 - 67" publicationUrl="http://er.lepidoptera.ro/20_2016/ER20201603_Rakosy_etal.pdf" refId="B30" refString="Rakosy, L, Stuening, D, Stănescu, M, Sommerer, M, 2016. The systematic position of Palaeocrocota ostrogovichi (Caradja, 1930) (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Ennominae). Entomologica romanica 20: 63 - 67, http://er.lepidoptera.ro/20_2016/ER20201603_Rakosy_etal.pdf" title="The systematic position of Palaeocrocota ostrogovichi (Caradja, 1930) (Lepidoptera: Geometridae, Ennominae)." url="http://er.lepidoptera.ro/20_2016/ER20201603_Rakosy_etal.pdf" volume="20" year="2016">
<normalizedToken id="CB84A2974B910C0C5AD7B106A8434E7F" originalValue="Rákosy">Rakosy</normalizedToken>
et al. (2016)
</bibRefCitation>
, but it could instead be synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="F89D7362CF00ACEB1DFE4E4DC9A47E27" authority="Duponchel, 1829" authorityName="Duponchel" authorityYear="1829" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Cleogene" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="rablensis" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rablensis">rablensis</taxonomicName>
if the occurrence of this taxon in the Cluj-Napoca area was ascertained.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="7F36E95F49656BA15EB059901E34835E" pageId="15" pageNumber="242">
<taxonomicName id="706A2EB5C949EAE5C4057255E9477235" authority="stehliki" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Isturgia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Isturgia roraria subsp. ab." order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="roraria" subSpecies="ab.">Isturgia roraria ab. stehliki</taxonomicName>
Bretschneider, 1954, Ent. Z. 64: 41, Germany, [Saxony-Anhalt], Dessau [infrasubspecific: almost completely black form, obtained from a F2 generation, bred from normal-coloured 
<taxonomicName id="C7D6B438D3130A52B4D4D6C69723C148" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1776" class="Insecta" family="Geometridae" genus="Isturgia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="roraria" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="242" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roraria">roraria</taxonomicName>
parents].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
